detailed_spec: Polypropylene Mesh is well knitted polypropylene material with standard heavy weight offers maximum tissue support and flexible scar for superior patient comfort. Strong and durable polypropylene material maintains consistent strength. The mesh is non-absorbable and is sterilized using ethylene oxide. Polypropylene mesh has a pore size of 1.0 mm x 1.2 mm, a weight of 100 gsm, and a thickness of 0.48 mm. It has a burst strength of 106.3 N/cm2.

title: Powered Hernia Mesh Fixation Device Non Absorbable- 15 tacks
short_spec: Powered Hernia Mesh Fixation Device Non Absorbable- 15 tacks
detailed_spec: Powered tacker offer is smart choice for faster, secure mesh fixation. Inline handle design with rubber grip. Powered hernia mesh fixation device non-absorbable tacks made from titanium. It is helical-shaped hook design to ensure strong fixation, with each device containing 15 tacks. The device operates via a powered firing mechanism activated by a push-button for consistent deployment and includes a tack counter display for precise application tracking. The fixation cannula measures 36 cm in length with a 5mm tube diameter

short_spec: Powered Hernia Mesh Fixation Device Absorbable- 15 tacks
detailed_spec: Powered tacker offer is smart choice for faster, secure mesh fixation. Inline handle design with rubber grip. Powered hernia mesh fixation device absorbable tacks made from Polyglycolide-Co-Lactide (PGLA). It is screw-shaped hook design to ensure strong fixation, with each device containing 15 tacks. The device operates via a powered firing mechanism activated by a push-button, offering consistent deployment. It includes a tack counter display for precise application tracking. The fixation cannula measures 36 cm in length with a 5mm tube diameter. The absorbable tacks are designed to be fully absorbed within 5 to 6 months

short_spec: Polypropylene+Polyglecaprone Partially absorbable monofilament knitted COMPOSITE MESH SIZE 10CM X 15CM
detailed_spec: The mesh is a knitted, composite-type mesh designed to be partially absorbable and lightweight. It is constructed primarily from polypropylene, with a layer composed of polyglecaprone to enhance absorbability. The mesh is available in square or rectangular shapes with size 10 cm x 15 cm. It has a weight of 88 grams per square meter (gsm), with a pore size of 2.0 mm x 2.0 mm and a minimum polypropylene content of 30 gsm. The mesh has a thickness of 0.5 mm and demonstrates an initial burst strength of 313 N/cm2. After the absorption of the polyglecaprone 25 layer, the burst strength is reduced to 215 N/cm2. The mesh is sterilized using ethylene oxide

title: Polypropylene Anatomical Mesh (3D MESH) SIZE-L(11.5CM X 16.2CM) LEFT
short_spec: Polypropylene Anatomical Mesh (3D MESH) SIZE-L(11.5CM X 16.2CM) LEFT
detailed_spec: Anatomical mesh (3D Mesh) is made from non-absorbable monofilament polypropylene textile and has a large pore design. Flexible 3D construction allows a prompt fibroblastic response through the interstices of the mesh. Its unique 3D design conforms to the inguinal anatomy. There is a blue monofilament orientation marker (M) and arrow. Polypropylene anatomical (3D) mesh has a pore size of 1.0 mm x 1.5 mm, a weight of 1.56g and a thickness of 0.55 mm. It has a uniaxial tensile strength of 65 N, a biaxial tensile strength of 100 N, and a burst strength of 93.16 N/cm2. The mesh is sterilized using ethylene oxide.

detailed_spec: Polypropylene Mesh is well knitted polypropylene material with standard heavy weight offers maximum tissue support and flexible scar for superior patient comfort. Strong and durable polypropylene material maintains consistent strength. The mesh is non-absorbable and is sterilized using ethylene oxide.
